narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Good class -- lots of reading but interesting reading. I would recommend it.
I would recommend the course to anyone remotely interested in history. It is very important subject matter.

- Great class on slavery.- Covers different aspects of the trade - economic, political, social etc.- Readings are interesting- Professor Rugemer is a great guy who makes the debate interesting and engaging without the need to forcing the subject down your throat
I would absolutely recommend this seminar to a fellow student. Professor Rugemer is a very fair, not to mention knowledgeable and engaging.
I would recommend it to someone who is genuinely interested in the material.
